FT  01 JUN 94 / International Company News: Shiseido ahead at pre-tax level
Shiseido, the leading Japanese cosmetics maker, reported that
non-consolidated pre-tax profits for the year to March rose 0.1 per cent to
Y32.4bn (Dollars 309.75m), writes Emiko Terazono in Tokyo. It suffered a 2.3
per cent decline in sales to Y391.1bn. For the year to next March, the
company expects pre-tax profits flat at Y32.5bn, on a 1 per cent rise in
sales to Y395bn.
